HEADWORD: Tercet
<hw>Ter"cet</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. It.
<ets>terzetto</ets>, dim. of <ets>terzo</ets>, third, L.
<ets>tertius</ets>. See <er>Tierce</er>, and cf.
<er>Terzetto</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A
triplet.</def> <rj><au>Hiles.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Poetry)</fld> <def>A triplet; a group of three
lines.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tercine</ent>⟦br⟧
